self-administered areas and urban centres influenced Shan State voters to choose the USDP. The results of the election for ethnic affairs ministers approximate those of the nationwide results. Like the national and regional election results, the Rakhine as well as ethnic groups in Shan State voted for candidates from ethnic parties, indicating that the agenda of these ethnic parties is particularly important for those populations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCampaigns & Elections. 0aElections—Burma—Rakhine State. 0aElections—Burma—Shan State. 0aMinorities—Political activity—Burma. 0aPolitical parties—Burma—Rakhine State. 0aPolitical parties—Burma—Shan State. 0aRakhine State (Burma)—Politics and government. 0aShan State (Burma)—Politics and government. 4aCampaigns & Elections. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Campaigns & Elections.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066299308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060667608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101240uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981469590940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814695909423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814695909.jpg  a978-3-11-060667-6  ISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066299-3  ISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  a